Panchulei is the nom de plume of Chilean cartoonist and publisher Francisca Cárcamo Rojas. More of her work can be found at her website, panchulei.com, or on Instagram, where she is @panchulei Translation by James Scorer, senior lecturer in Latin American cultural studies at the University of Manchester and project lead for Comics and the Latin American City, funded by The Leverhulme Trust If you’re an illustrator or graphic artist with an idea for The Illustrated City series, email us at Cities@theguardian.com Follow Guardian Cities on Twitter, Facebook and Instagram to join the discussion, catch up on our best stories or sign up for our weekly newsletter